<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,1862,2008]" lastBlockId="22.[151,1436,152,338]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
A total of 
<specimenCount box="[324,499,1902,1928]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="generic">
<number box="[324,367,1902,1928]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="116.0">116</number>
specimens
</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[561,668,1902,1928]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="egg">
<number box="[561,605,1902,1928]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="106.0">106</number>
eggs
</specimenCount>
were isolated from MR samples. This species, belonging to the 
<taxonomicName box="[151,262,1943,1968]" class="Eutardigrada" family="Macrobiotidae" genus="Macrobiotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Parachela" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="hufelandi">
<emphasis box="[151,262,1943,1968]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">hufelandi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, showed animals and eggs morphologies as in the original description (
<bibRefCitation author="Bertolani" pageId="21" pageNumber="28" refString="Bertolani, R. &amp; Rebecchi, L. (1993) A revision of Macrobiotus hufelandi group (Tardigrada, Macrobiotidae), with some observations on the taxonomic characthers of eutardigrades. Zoologica Scripta, 22 (2), 127 - 152." type="journal article" year="1993">
Bertolani &amp; Rebecchi 
<number box="[151,214,1982,2008]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1993.0">1993</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Some specimens showed weak buccal armature with a clearly visible transverse crest system yet powerless anterior and posterior bands of teeth. Smooth or irregular lunule margins in the double-claws at the fourth pair of legs. Ocular spots were in 
<number box="[622,653,192,218]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="40.0">40</number>
% of the total specimens, while in 
<number box="[1054,1085,192,218]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="60.0">60</number>
% it was not possible to determine their presence or absence. Body size range was 
<number box="[787,930,232,258]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="627.0" valueMax="1012.0" valueMin="242.0">242 to 1012</number>
μm, mean 
<number box="[1065,1109,232,258]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="568.0">568</number>
μm (SD 
<number box="[1221,1269,232,258]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="165.0">165</number>
). This species has been cited only for Europe. This is the first time it has been found in the Iberian Peninsula (
<tableCitation box="[1262,1352,272,298]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,239,1706,1730]" captionTargetBox="[159,1400,1802,1996]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="TABLE 2. Tardigrada species found in the Sierra de Guadarrama. New records (NR) for Europe (Eur), the Iberian Peninsula (IbPn), Spain (Spn) and Madrid Province (Mad) are indicated." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF5C665F3D5AFF91FF689BECFC06F97C" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" tableUuid="DF5C665F3D5AFF91FF689BECFC06F97C">
Table 
<number box="[1335,1352,272,298]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="2.0">2</number>
</tableCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName class="Eutardigrada" family="Macrobiotidae" genus="Macrobiotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Parachela" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="macrocalix">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Macrobiotus macrocalix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was observed at seven sampling points (Table 
<number box="[936,952,312,338]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="3.0">3</number>
).
</paragraph>
